## Frequently Asked Questions

**Which is the best SEO company in the UK?**

There is no single best SEO company: the right choice depends on your business type, budget, and growth goals. For consumer brands wanting links and coverage, Rise at Seven or Aira lead the market. For pure technical SEO depth, Blue Array, Screaming Frog, or Reboot Online. For AI search optimisation (AEO/GEO), Sunny Patel SEO is the only UK consultant with documented AI-search lead conversions. For SMEs and B2B businesses wanting a direct senior consultant rather than an agency, Sunny Patel SEO offers a different model. Use the comparison table at the top of this page to match your situation to the right provider type.

**How much do UK SEO companies charge?**

UK SEO company pricing typically ranges from £1,000/month for smaller independent specialists to £5,000-10,000+/month for enterprise agency retainers. Monthly retainers between £1,500-£3,000 represent the mid-market where most SMEs operate. One-off technical audits typically range from £500-£2,500 depending on site complexity. Avoid agencies quoting below £800/month: at that price point, you are getting templated work rather than a genuine strategy.

**How do I know if an SEO company is reputable?**

Ask for Search Console data from a client in your industry. Any agency that cannot or will not provide verifiable GSC or Analytics evidence from past clients is a red flag. Check whether they have published case studies with real traffic numbers, not just testimonials. Verify their Google Business Profile reviews. Ask specifically who will be working on your account day-to-day: the senior pitch, junior delivery model is widespread in UK agencies.

**What is an independent SEO agency?**

An independent SEO agency is owned by its founders or employees rather than a marketing network or holding group. Independence tends to keep senior people closer to client work because there is no group-level pressure to scale accounts with junior staff. On this list, Propellernet is employee-owned and Sunny Patel SEO is a single independent consultant. Whoever you shortlist, ask who owns the company and who will actually work on your account.

**What is the difference between an SEO agency and an SEO consultant?**

An SEO agency is a company with multiple employees working across many clients. An independent SEO consultant is a single expert working directly on your account. Agencies offer more execution capacity for large content programmes; consultants offer direct senior access without the account management layer. For most SMEs, a consultant at the same monthly investment as an agency delivers more strategic value because every pound goes to the person doing the work rather than company overhead.

**How long does it take for SEO to work?**

Technical SEO fixes typically show results within 4-8 weeks. Local SEO improvements (Google Maps, near-me searches) typically take 3-6 months. Building competitive organic authority for primary commercial keywords takes 6-12 months. These timelines apply regardless of whether you use an agency or consultant: they are determined by Google's evaluation cycles, not headcount.

**Are paid SEO agency directories reliable?**

Most UK SEO agency directories (Clutch, DesignRush, and various "top 10" lists) operate on a pay-to-feature model where agencies pay £500-£5,000 for placement. Rankings on these platforms reflect marketing budget, not SEO quality. This list does not operate that way: every company listed here was selected on published methodology, verifiable results, and client evidence. Always check whether the list you are reading generates revenue from the companies it recommends.

